    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so if the effectiveness is widely accepted, how do planners usually address the arguments from people who say it's basically just a regressive tax on workers who live further out and have no choice but to drive? is there a way to make it \"fair\" or is it just an unavoidable trade-off?",
