      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Planners address this \"regressive tax\" concern by implementing equity measures, such as exemptions or discounts for low-income residents and essential workers. Another common strategy is earmarking the generated revenue specifically for enhancing transit services in underserved outer boroughs. While achieving perfect fairness is challenging, these mitigation strategies aim to offset the financial burden and provide viable alternatives for those who have limited mobility choices.",
      "source": "target",
